    {
      "id": "K370f95sWAYubPwpikVnk",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 20061.501977550688,
      "y": 777.1020652850221,
      "width": 175.85674304757424,
      "height": 31.25066652360043,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIq",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2076168705,
      "version": 1891,
      "versionNonce": 1152611425,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776079724306,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1 - You type something in Copilot like: “Open my HYSYS case and add a Heater called E-100.”\n2 - VS Code/Copilot uses MCP to find a server and its tools.\n3 - VS Code starts the MCP server by executing what’s configured in mcp.json (details below).\n4 - The MCP server process runs your .NET app and communicates over stdio (stdin/stdout), not HTTP. The server wiring is in Program.cs.\n5 - When Copilot calls a tool (e.g. hysys_open_case), the method in HysysTools.cs runs.\n6 - That tool delegates to the COM wrapper in HysysService.cs, which:\n --->  tries to attach to an already-running HYSYS instance first (important for your “Hysys.exe is already running” scenario),\n --->  otherwise starts a new HYSYS COM instance,\n --->  then performs operations like opening a case, adding unit ops, adding/removing streams.",
      "fontSize": 2.7778370243200388,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1 - You type something in Copilot like: “Open my HYSYS case and add a Heater called E-100.”\n2 - VS Code/Copilot uses MCP to find a server and its tools.\n3 - VS Code starts the MCP server by executing what’s configured in mcp.json (details below).\n4 - The MCP server process runs your .NET app and communicates over stdio (stdin/stdout), not HTTP. The server wiring is in Program.cs.\n5 - When Copilot calls a tool (e.g. hysys_open_case), the method in HysysTools.cs runs.\n6 - That tool delegates to the COM wrapper in HysysService.cs, which:\n --->  tries to attach to an already-running HYSYS instance first (important for your “Hysys.exe is already running” scenario),\n --->  otherwise starts a new HYSYS COM instance,\n --->  then performs operations like opening a case, adding unit ops, adding/removing streams.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "P7GzFF_hYmpBtJp_R3L1u",
      "type": "line",
      "x": 19750.612113821975,
      "y": 792.367232481106,
      "width": 128.26334569924836,
      "height": 2.977980960162971,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "dotted",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIr",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 2
      },
