    },
    {
      "id": "iYdxbTVBTlgT-gJWtvJV9",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 19711.185387003705,
      "y": 795.0499331875028,
      "width": 77.04568619579877,
      "height": 10.887889020327135,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#f08c00",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIs",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1564296737,
      "version": 1164,
      "versionNonce": 1113100321,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776079724306,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "mcp.json is the “wiring file” that tells VS Code:\n-->   There is an MCP server named aspentech-eng-mcp\n-->   How to start it (here: run dotnet run --project ...csproj)",
      "fontSize": 2.903437072087236,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "mcp.json is the “wiring file” that tells VS Code:\n-->   There is an MCP server named aspentech-eng-mcp\n-->   How to start it (here: run dotnet run --project ...csproj)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "EpwmHjMGnROfmwINipIAo",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 19639.190138105572,
      "y": 742.3436946694519,
      "width": 101.54352817918496,
      "height": 12.394140131997107,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#f08c00",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIt",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 563906017,
      "version": 1312,
      "versionNonce": 923369103,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776079719623,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Big role: it turns “generic Copilot” into “Copilot that knows your domain workflow.” Without it, Copilot can still\ndiscover MCP tools, but it’s more likely to:\n-->    call the wrong tool,\n-->    guess parameters incorrectly,\n-->    or skip important steps (like opening a case first).",
      "fontSize": 1.983062421119538,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Big role: it turns “generic Copilot” into “Copilot that knows your domain workflow.” Without it, Copilot can still discover MCP tools, but it’s more likely to:\n-->    call the wrong tool,\n-->    guess parameters incorrectly,\n-->    or skip important steps (like opening a case first).",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "YXzP8heyzqL9XAGwanpWT",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 19639.021830755893,
      "y": 727.7819136961762,
      "width": 101.54352817918496,
      "height": 12.394140131997112,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "hachure",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bIu",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1107320495,
      "version": 1373,
      "versionNonce": 1771623599,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776079719623,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "How it fits with MCP: MCP provides the tools; SKILL.md provides the “operating manual” so Copilot uses those\ntools correctly.\nCurrently Partially matching:\n--->    SKILL.md currently lists only:                   open/close/add/delete unit op.\n--->    HysysTools.cs implements those plus      add/delete stream tools.",
      "fontSize": 1.983062421119538,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "How it fits with MCP: MCP provides the tools; SKILL.md provides the “operating manual” so Copilot uses those tools correctly.\nCurrently Partially matching:\n--->    SKILL.md currently lists only:                   open/close/add/delete unit op.\n--->    HysysTools.cs implements those plus      add/delete stream tools.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
